- Hey, your pain is my pain,
bro.

13:24.671 --> 13:26.004
Bring it in.

13:29.976 --> 13:31.576
(phone chimes)

13:31.645 --> 13:34.378
Look up moonshine campground,
nova scotia.

13:34.414 --> 13:36.714
(seagulls cry)

13:36.783 --> 13:38.649
(whirring)

13:40.320 --> 13:42.119
(waves lap, footsteps thud)

13:43.790 --> 13:45.189
- Are you okay?

13:45.258 --> 13:47.258
- Okay is a relative state,
pops.

13:47.260 --> 13:49.193
I'm just trying to get through
the day without having a drink,

13:49.196 --> 13:51.962
But man, if I couldn't chug
a 24, and it's not even noon.

13:52.999 --> 13:54.932
- Is that why you're doing
something

13:55.068 --> 13:57.202
I've never seen before?
- What's that?

13:57.337 --> 13:59.370
- Your job, son.

13:59.505 --> 14:01.606
- I had no idea it was such
a solid distraction.

14:01.608 --> 14:03.041
I should've started years ago.

14:03.043 --> 14:05.243
- That would've been good.

14:06.813 --> 14:08.613
- Crystal moved out.

14:08.748 --> 14:10.814
And sammy hates me.

14:10.851 --> 14:12.316
This job is all I have now.

14:14.754 --> 14:16.421
- For what it's worth,
you got me, kid.

14:20.694 --> 14:26.964
♪♪♪

14:27.000 --> 14:29.100
(birds chirp)

14:29.235 --> 14:31.269
(shakers rattle)

14:32.806 --> 14:34.639
Bea: As you lay upon the earth,

14:34.708 --> 14:36.974
I summon the rest
of the elements.

14:38.178 --> 14:39.911
Air.

14:41.348 --> 14:43.614
- Fire, but I'm gonna need this
back as soon as we're done.

14:45.652 --> 14:47.184
- And the sea.

14:47.254 --> 14:49.387
(water splashes)

14:49.522 --> 14:51.388
- I literally have a spruce
branch up my butt,

14:51.424 --> 14:52.856
And not in a good way.

14:52.893 --> 14:54.725
- There's gotta be a more
efficient way of beating

14:54.761 --> 14:55.993
Some sense into her,

14:56.029 --> 14:57.795
Like, actually beating some
sense into her?

14:57.864 --> 15:00.365
- Hail to the guardians
of the watchtower

15:00.367 --> 15:03.334
From the north, south,
east, and west.

15:03.370 --> 15:05.670
Hear me! Hear us!

15:06.773 --> 15:09.107
Bea: What the hell?!
- (sighs)

15:09.242 --> 15:11.609
- It's from "the craft." 1996.

15:11.611 --> 15:13.745
- I was thinking more
"fight club."

15:13.880 --> 15:16.347
Bea: Usually, felicia and I
would just chant,

15:16.482 --> 15:19.383
"five flip efforts"

15:19.419 --> 15:21.185
Over and over again.
- And that means?

15:21.321 --> 15:23.955
- It's an anagram for
"eff off evil spirits."

15:25.224 --> 15:27.558
(whispers) five flip efforts.

15:27.693 --> 15:29.693
<i> Five flip efforts.</i>

15:29.729 --> 15:31.696
Nora, rhian, bea: (chanting)
five flip efforts.

15:31.831 --> 15:33.064
Five flip efforts.

15:34.134 --> 15:36.567
Five flip efforts.

15:36.569 --> 15:38.836
Five flip efforts.

15:38.905 --> 15:40.838
Five flip efforts.

15:40.907 --> 15:42.507
- You know this is your fault,
right?

15:42.642 --> 15:44.475
- Just tell them why
you're laundering money.

15:44.544 --> 15:46.143
And why you got all
boxcar bertha,

15:46.145 --> 15:47.812
And jacked the crustaceans.
- No,

15:47.814 --> 15:49.013
I don't want to involve them.

15:49.148 --> 15:51.215
- Oh, how very "bea" of you.
- Shut up!

15:51.351 --> 15:53.084
- You shut me up.
I'm in your head.

15:53.153 --> 15:55.019
- Shit! I am crazy.

15:55.154 --> 15:56.988
- You think nobody can do
this better than you?

15:57.123 --> 15:59.257
You think, you like the weight
of the world on your shoulder.

15:59.259 --> 16:01.025
Kid, you've got to get over
this martyr complex.

16:01.160 --> 16:03.927
- No, what I've gotta do
is pay a massive tax bill.

16:03.964 --> 16:05.663
- Secrets and lies.

16:05.665 --> 16:07.732
You know how this ends,
don't you?

16:07.801 --> 16:09.800
Nora, rhian, bea: Five flip
efforts.

16:09.836 --> 16:11.202
Five flip efforts.

16:11.337 --> 16:13.738
- Yeah, I do.

16:13.740 --> 16:15.606
Nora, rhian, bea: Five
flip efforts.

16:15.642 --> 16:17.074
Five flip efforts.

16:18.144 --> 16:19.877
Five flip efforts.

16:22.549 --> 16:24.615
Ia shrieks, groans)

16:24.617 --> 16:26.017
(screams) whoa!

16:26.019 --> 16:28.285
Damn! Ew!

16:28.321 --> 16:31.188
(sobs) ew! Oh!

16:31.190 --> 16:34.025
Felicia: (laughs)
that's shit.

16:34.027 --> 16:37.094
- (sighs) go away!

16:37.096 --> 16:39.163
I have it under control.

16:39.232 --> 16:40.964
(sighs, gasps)

16:41.001 --> 16:42.633
- You can't run from
yourself, lidz.

16:42.702 --> 16:44.168
- I'm sure as hell gonna try.

16:44.170 --> 16:47.038
(screams)
oh no!

16:47.040 --> 16:48.506
<i> Daniel: How are you</i>
<i> not sweating?</i>

16:48.508 --> 16:50.174
Like, do you not have pores?

16:50.176 --> 16:51.976
- Stress induces sweat.

16:52.045 --> 16:54.678
- Can I just step outside
to get a breeze?

16:54.748 --> 16:57.314
I promise I'm not gonna run
or retaliate.

16:58.485 --> 17:00.984
I'm a half-jewish architect
from brooklyn.

17:01.021 --> 17:02.519
The scariest thing about me

17:02.555 --> 17:04.255
Is occasional irritable bowel
syndrome.

17:04.257 --> 17:05.923
Please.

17:06.059 --> 17:08.659
Lidia is the mother
of my children.

17:08.795 --> 17:11.062
I took a vow to defend her.

17:11.064 --> 17:13.664
Surely that's something
you can understand.

17:13.666 --> 17:15.466
Vows? Codes?

17:15.502 --> 17:17.401
Blood oaths?

17:19.939 --> 17:23.407
You need to tell me
what is going on.

17:23.443 --> 17:26.210
You tell me right now,
or I swear to god...

17:26.212 --> 17:28.378
(sighs)

17:29.449 --> 17:31.282
I will call my lawyer.

17:31.284 --> 17:33.217
- Lawyers are not
gonna solve this.

17:35.288 --> 17:37.187
Sit.

17:39.092 --> 17:40.958
- I'd prefer to stand.

17:42.829 --> 17:44.362
- Now.

17:44.364 --> 17:46.831
- Fine. I will sit.

17:48.101 --> 17:50.200
But only because heat rises.

17:54.707 --> 17:58.109
- Okay, lidia and I may
have done a deal

17:58.111 --> 18:00.478
That pissed off some people.

18:00.613 --> 18:03.714
The leblancs, who may have
taken her as retaliation.

18:06.018 --> 18:07.485
- (gasps) oh my god!

18:07.620 --> 18:09.353
- My guys are out
looking for her.

18:09.422 --> 18:11.322
- We should be out
looking for her!

18:11.324 --> 18:13.724
Crystal: Excuse me!
What are you doing here?!

18:13.726 --> 18:15.993
What are you doing here?!
(gasps)

18:16.062 --> 18:18.562
What is he doing here?!

18:20.600 --> 18:22.799
- What are you doing here?

18:22.836 --> 18:25.369
- Uh, looking for lidia.
- Why?

18:25.371 --> 18:27.505
- It's none of your business.
- Crystal, where is she?

18:27.640 --> 18:29.740
- It is definitely none
of your business!

18:31.111 --> 18:32.876
Oh, wait.

18:32.912 --> 18:34.611
Did something happen to lidia?

18:35.714 --> 18:37.448
- That's not why you're here?

18:37.517 --> 18:39.249
- Well, no, I'm here to give
her the first installment

18:39.285 --> 18:40.751
Of my loan payment

18:40.753 --> 18:42.486
For my crystal clean van.

18:42.489 --> 18:44.755
- I think your mother took
lidia as payback

18:44.791 --> 18:46.990
For us hijacking her truck.

18:48.328 --> 18:50.761
- Oh.

18:50.797 --> 18:53.096
That wouldn't surprise me.

18:55.034 --> 19:00.371
♪♪♪

19:00.373 --> 19:04.175
Look, I know that you know
how dangerous my mother is,

19:04.177 --> 19:05.909
And I know that you know
that she knows

19:05.945 --> 19:07.578
That you jacked her snow crabs

19:07.614 --> 19:09.580
To purposefully to start
a turf war.

19:09.616 --> 19:11.349
So if you know what's good
for you,

19:11.351 --> 19:13.517
You will let me go,
I will let her know,

19:13.520 --> 19:15.252
And then maybe, just maybe,

19:15.321 --> 19:18.055
You will make it out
of this campground alive.

19:18.191 --> 19:20.023
You know?

19:22.328 --> 19:24.462
- Or I can keep you here

19:24.597 --> 19:26.763
Until your mother tells us
what she did with lidia.

19:29.002 --> 19:31.936
Until I know she's safe,
nobody leaves.

19:33.873 --> 19:35.672
- Cool.

19:35.708 --> 19:40.344
♪♪♪

19:40.346 --> 19:43.046
<i> Bea: Lidia!</i>

19:43.082 --> 19:44.681
Nora: Lidia?

19:44.717 --> 19:46.617
- Lidia!

19:48.421 --> 19:50.821
- Well, one thing's
for damn sure,

19:50.857 --> 19:53.357
She won't survive if we don't
find her by sundown.

19:53.426 --> 19:55.492
- The highway's not that far.

19:55.528 --> 19:57.428
- Oh, she got lost in a garden
centre once.

19:57.497 --> 19:59.964
I found her in a fetal position
behind the dwarf hydrangeas.

20:00.099 --> 20:02.900
- We must obey the three
rules of tracking:

20:02.902 --> 20:05.102
One, be quiet, and listen.

20:05.238 --> 20:07.071
Two, know the tracks well.

20:07.206 --> 20:08.439
Three...

20:08.508 --> 20:10.575
Know the dung better.

20:10.710 --> 20:12.977
Where I go, I go alone.

20:13.112 --> 20:14.711
- Perfect, because I am going
no further

20:14.747 --> 20:16.313
Into those woods
with these shoes.

20:16.449 --> 20:18.582
- No one should go anywhere
in those shoes.

20:18.585 --> 20:20.918
And as for you, I'm not letting
a knocked-up whack job

20:20.920 --> 20:22.720
Go out there alone.
- No choice.

20:22.722 --> 20:24.922
Neither of you know
dung for shit.

20:24.924 --> 20:28.793
♪♪♪

20:31.130 --> 20:35.399
♪♪♪

20:39.272 --> 20:41.204
(echoing howl)

20:41.241 --> 20:42.406
(crow caws)

20:42.442 --> 20:44.207
(birds chirp)

20:45.945 --> 20:49.179
♪♪♪

20:52.752 --> 20:54.718
(tambourine rattles)

20:56.055 --> 20:57.754
It's a dried-up blonde hair

20:59.292 --> 21:01.025
With a dark root,
and a split end.

21:02.762 --> 21:04.561
Some mother on a stress bender.

21:08.001 --> 21:09.466
Fear!

21:10.603 --> 21:12.570
I've got you now, lidz!

21:13.706 --> 21:15.639
(loud whoop)

21:15.642 --> 21:17.508
<i> (animal grunts distantly)</i>

21:17.643 --> 21:19.643
(breathes heavily)

21:19.646 --> 21:21.679
Ow!

21:23.783 --> 21:25.616
<i> Nora: So, mom...</i>

21:25.685 --> 21:28.919
The dude at ryan's
dinnervention...

21:28.921 --> 21:30.687
- Davide.
- Davide!

21:30.689 --> 21:32.723
Now, you'd think an actor
would be able to do

21:32.792 --> 21:34.792
A decent british accent, no?

21:34.861 --> 21:36.527
- He really is quite brilliant.

21:38.130 --> 21:40.664
- Whoa, mama has a lady-boner.

21:40.667 --> 21:42.533
- Get your mind out
of the gutter.

21:42.535 --> 21:45.536
- The gutter is a key
tool of my trade.

21:47.206 --> 21:48.872
- Things with you and terry
seem cozy.

21:48.941 --> 21:51.275
- Yeah, well,

21:51.277 --> 21:53.611
Real relationships are harder
than secret love affairs,

21:53.613 --> 21:55.412
Who'dve thunk?

21:55.414 --> 21:56.613
- You only really get to know
someone

21:56.683 --> 21:58.883
Through the intimate
day-to-day.

21:59.018 --> 22:00.784
- The man hikes at dawn.

22:00.820 --> 22:02.887
Flosses after every meal,

22:02.889 --> 22:04.621
I can only take so much
hygiene.

22:04.657 --> 22:08.191
- So... Not the love of your
life, after all?

22:11.030 --> 22:14.098
- Is there any wine
in this old cabin?

22:15.835 --> 22:19.570
♪♪♪

22:19.639 --> 22:22.239
- (sighs) end of an era.

22:22.375 --> 22:24.108
Mmm!

22:24.243 --> 22:26.610
Felicia and I bottled
this ourselves.

22:26.646 --> 22:28.311
(laughs quietly)

22:28.348 --> 22:29.914
It might be vinegar
by now, but...

22:29.916 --> 22:31.481
It should do the trick.

22:31.517 --> 22:33.917
- Okay, well, here's to...

22:33.986 --> 22:36.320
(cork pops) "doing the trick."

22:38.190 --> 22:39.823
Mm! That'll do it.

22:40.926 --> 22:42.860
(birds chirp)

22:42.929 --> 22:44.828
(leaves rustle)

22:48.735 --> 22:50.000
- (sighs)

22:50.002 --> 22:52.203
Okay, sister,
I am feral,

22:52.205 --> 22:55.739
Hungry, and some- ah-
plant just gave me a rash.

22:55.742 --> 22:58.208
I am not in the mood
for bullshit.

22:58.244 --> 23:00.711
Tell me which way
to the highway, now!

23:00.713 --> 23:02.980
- (sobs quietly)

23:04.117 --> 23:05.682
- Rhian?

23:05.752 --> 23:08.152
Are you crying?
- No.

23:08.221 --> 23:11.354
I was just making these sounds
to lure in my prey,

23:11.391 --> 23:13.256
And, see, sucker, it worked.

23:14.694 --> 23:17.261
- What's going on?

23:17.396 --> 23:19.529
- Just ah,

23:19.565 --> 23:21.498
Dehydration cramps
from hunting you.

23:21.567 --> 23:24.101
- That's not a thing,
I don't think.

23:24.103 --> 23:28.038
♪♪♪

23:28.107 --> 23:30.541
- I felt a twinge.

23:30.676 --> 23:33.210
I went to pee,
and there was blood.

23:34.580 --> 23:36.279
(sobs)
- oh.

23:39.051 --> 23:41.051
- (sighs)

23:41.120 --> 23:43.053
(sobs)

23:43.055 --> 23:45.189
I know the baby is just
a cluster of poppy seed

23:45.324 --> 23:47.124
Sized-cells, but...

23:47.259 --> 23:50.126
It was my cluster.

23:50.163 --> 23:51.895
(sobs)

23:52.999 --> 23:54.731
- Okay, come here.

23:54.767 --> 23:56.566
- (sobs)

24:02.742 --> 24:05.142
- So, how long has this
been going on?

24:06.245 --> 24:08.278
You and lidia?

24:10.149 --> 24:11.515
- A couple weeks.

24:11.584 --> 24:14.684
- Oh. I didn't think
you were her type.

24:14.720 --> 24:16.487
- Why?

24:16.622 --> 24:18.655
Because I don't treat her
like an afterthought?

24:18.724 --> 24:20.690
- They say you should never
make someone a priority

24:20.726 --> 24:23.093
Who only considers you
an option.

24:23.095 --> 24:25.296
But they also say that
you find a partner

24:25.298 --> 24:28.132
Who reminds you of your mom,
so, that's not me.

24:28.134 --> 24:29.633
(laughs)

24:30.770 --> 24:32.369
Oh, wait.

24:32.438 --> 24:34.104
Is ryan like my mom?

24:35.508 --> 24:38.042
They both get into trouble,
and expect me to bail them out,

24:38.177 --> 24:40.844
They're brunette,
with super-toned arms,

24:40.847 --> 24:42.579
And a thing for boobs!

24:43.950 --> 24:46.250
- So based on you dating lidia,

24:46.319 --> 24:48.385
I guess that would also make
your mom a demanding,

24:48.454 --> 24:50.254
Impulsive, over-talking a-type?

24:50.323 --> 24:51.788
- I think you mean a smoking
hot fox

24:51.858 --> 24:53.890
Who's a dynamo in the sack.

24:55.494 --> 24:57.594
I grew up in a trailer
with really thin walls.

24:57.663 --> 25:00.531
- Okay, that is all kinds
of traumatizing.

25:00.666 --> 25:02.199
- Why?

25:02.334 --> 25:04.068
Do the natural impulses
of the human body

25:04.203 --> 25:07.104
Make you uncomfortable, daniel?

25:07.239 --> 25:08.739
- What about your mom?

25:08.874 --> 25:10.641
Was she a cheater, too?

25:10.643 --> 25:13.944
- No. My dad, actually,
but my mom...

25:15.381 --> 25:17.414
My mom was a-a real
piece of work.

25:17.550 --> 25:19.216
- Ugh. Mommy issues alert!

25:19.285 --> 25:20.684
Mommy issues alert!

25:20.686 --> 25:23.287
No wonder you ruined
your marriage.

25:24.757 --> 25:27.024
- Are you having a seizure?

25:27.026 --> 25:28.892
- No, I-- (sighs)

25:28.961 --> 25:31.295
I really have to pee.

25:33.199 --> 25:37.701
♪♪♪

25:37.836 --> 25:39.936
- What? What?!

25:40.973 --> 25:45.108
♪♪♪

25:45.177 --> 25:46.977
(door opens)

25:50.550 --> 25:52.115
- So why did you ruin
your marriage?

25:53.185 --> 25:54.585
<i> Crystal: Because he's one</i>
<i> of those men</i>

25:54.720 --> 25:56.920
<i> That has all of the nice</i>
<i> things,</i>

25:56.923 --> 25:58.655
<i> But he still wants more nice</i>
<i> things.</i>

25:58.791 --> 26:01.325
<i> Even though most people</i>
<i> don't have any nice things!</i>

26:01.327 --> 26:03.160
- Maybe she's right.

26:03.162 --> 26:05.029
I had it all.

26:05.031 --> 26:06.963
But marcie, my assistant,

26:06.999 --> 26:08.933
Oh my god,
that sounds so cliché,

26:09.068 --> 26:11.668
She made me feel like
I was more.

26:11.704 --> 26:13.470
Also cliché.

26:13.539 --> 26:15.239
Anyway, nobody knew,

26:15.374 --> 26:17.207
So nobody was getting hurt,
right?

26:17.243 --> 26:18.942
But in retrospect,

26:18.945 --> 26:20.677
I was hurting everyone
the entire time.

26:20.746 --> 26:23.013
I ruined my own life.

26:24.083 --> 26:25.649
<i> Crystal: Nailed it!</i>

26:25.784 --> 26:28.018
<i>(scraping, clattering noises)</i>

26:31.423 --> 26:33.357
Shit!

26:33.359 --> 26:36.693
♪♪♪

26:36.762 --> 26:39.396
Robin!

26:41.433 --> 26:44.201
♪♪♪

26:44.336 --> 26:46.403
(car rumbles)

26:48.541 --> 26:50.073
(birds chirp)

26:52.078 --> 26:59.049
♪♪♪

26:59.085 --> 27:04.721
♪♪♪

27:04.857 --> 27:07.157
(waves lap)

27:07.292 --> 27:09.393
(birds chirp)

27:11.463 --> 27:17.200
♪♪♪

27:17.236 --> 27:18.702
(waves laps)

27:18.771 --> 27:22.238
♪♪♪

27:24.810 --> 27:27.144
Eleanor: Okay. New song
content?

27:27.146 --> 27:29.546
Okay, what about animals
in captivity?

27:29.615 --> 27:31.381
- Cool.
- Lobsters go--

27:31.417 --> 27:33.951
Bruce! Bruce, come on,
let us play!

27:33.953 --> 27:36.086
- (sighs) you're not even old
enough to drink at a bar.

27:36.088 --> 27:38.222
No!
- We're old souls.

27:38.357 --> 27:39.956
And we've been through
a lot this summer.

27:39.992 --> 27:42.226
- Sure, you're wealthy,
white, educated kids.

27:42.228 --> 27:43.727
You've seen hard times.

27:43.862 --> 27:46.196
- We have a ton of originals.
- Like?

27:46.265 --> 27:48.499
- "big city," "cabin fever,"
"fire me,"

27:48.501 --> 27:50.401
"green sweater,"
"sexting my ex--"

27:50.536 --> 27:52.469
- Hmm. Dig deeper, kid.

27:52.538 --> 27:54.237
- (scoffs)

27:54.306 --> 27:56.272
- (sighs)

27:57.376 --> 27:59.443
- We could write about mom.
- Oh my god, yes.

27:59.445 --> 28:01.244
Artistic therapy, like,

28:01.280 --> 28:03.246
A way to express she's
gone totally batshit.

28:03.282 --> 28:05.782
"she said this would be
a vacation,

28:05.818 --> 28:07.584
Not a criminal ideation,

28:07.653 --> 28:09.520
Back where it all began,

28:09.522 --> 28:10.988
On the hunt for a smokin'
hot man--"

28:10.990 --> 28:12.456
- Yes, that's good.
- Okay, write that down.

28:12.591 --> 28:13.990
Write that down.

28:14.026 --> 28:15.992
Hey, can I help you?

28:16.028 --> 28:18.195
- Uh, a bottle of water,
please.

28:18.330 --> 28:19.863
- I'm protesting plastic.

28:19.998 --> 28:21.832
But I can give you a cup
for a quarter.

28:21.834 --> 28:23.933
- Deal.

28:25.003 --> 28:27.003
- Anything to eat?
- (laughs) nah.

28:27.039 --> 28:29.139
Thanks. I know how the clams
get fried in this place.

28:31.243 --> 28:33.143
I worked here one summer
when I was your age.

28:33.212 --> 28:35.345
- Oh, you must know
our mom, then.

28:35.347 --> 28:37.614
- You're nora's kids?
- Oh, I wish.

28:37.683 --> 28:39.516
Our mom's lidia.

28:39.585 --> 28:41.084
- Well, if you look around,

28:41.087 --> 28:42.753
My name is carved
in a wall somewhere.

28:42.888 --> 28:45.088
Best job ever.

28:45.157 --> 28:47.291
- For real?
- For reals.

28:47.426 --> 28:50.494
- Hmm, you worked here
and survived.

28:50.496 --> 28:53.329
- I didn't say that.
Thank you.

28:54.433 --> 28:56.533
- See ya.
- Bye.

28:56.569 --> 28:58.668
♪♪♪

28:58.704 --> 29:00.236
Huh.

29:00.272 --> 29:02.906
- Okay, did you get that?
- Yeah, "smoking hot man,"

29:03.041 --> 29:04.641
I know, I know.
- Write it again.

29:04.677 --> 29:06.643
(birds chirp)

29:06.779 --> 29:09.078
(wine sloshes)
- mm!

29:10.149 --> 29:13.784
Mm! Look, "lord of the lies"
returneth.

29:13.919 --> 29:16.386
Nice job.

29:18.957 --> 29:20.791
Who died?

29:25.698 --> 29:27.330
- We're never gonna find
these keys.

29:27.399 --> 29:29.165
- We are not stopping
until we find them.

29:29.201 --> 29:31.235
We need to get you
to the clinic.

29:31.237 --> 29:33.269
- Says the woman who threw
our only way out of here

29:33.305 --> 29:34.938
Into an impenetrable forest.

29:35.073 --> 29:36.673
- There's no point in rushing.

29:36.742 --> 29:37.941
I mean, if it happened,
it happened,

29:37.977 --> 29:39.843
There's nothing
that we can do now.

29:39.978 --> 29:42.679
- That's not true.
I spotted when I was pregnant.

29:42.748 --> 29:45.549
Oh god, one time, I bled
so much daniel fainted,

29:45.684 --> 29:47.217
Hit his head on the clawfoot
tub,

29:47.253 --> 29:48.885
And knocked himself out cold.

29:48.921 --> 29:50.854
The ambulance took us
to the hospital, and...

29:50.923 --> 29:52.723
It turned out we were
both fine.

29:52.858 --> 29:54.691
Well, me and the baby.

29:54.760 --> 29:56.693
They kept daniel for
concussion protocol.

29:56.829 --> 29:59.095
- It's my own fault,
I know that.

29:59.131 --> 30:01.898
- No. A lot of women
have miscarriages

30:02.034 --> 30:03.834
In their first trimester.

30:03.969 --> 30:06.736
We had one...

30:06.806 --> 30:08.639
Right before we found sammy.

30:10.976 --> 30:13.143
Eight weeks.
- Mom!

30:13.145 --> 30:15.278
God, I had no idea.

30:15.347 --> 30:17.547
You and dad were pregnant?

30:20.519 --> 30:23.119
- It's the only time this
family has ever been

30:23.155 --> 30:24.955
Nice to me.
- Oh, rhian.

30:25.024 --> 30:27.691
- Well, would you have baked me
oatcakes if I wasn't pregnant?

30:27.693 --> 30:30.594
Would you have answered phones

30:30.729 --> 30:32.262
And stuck daisies into a vase?

30:32.298 --> 30:35.565
Would lidia have given me
the keys to the moonshine?

30:35.601 --> 30:38.134
- Rhian, we do all that
for you because we love you.

30:38.170 --> 30:40.003
For the unique,

30:40.138 --> 30:42.539
Interesting person
that you are.

30:42.608 --> 30:44.674
We have more value than
just our wombs.

30:44.710 --> 30:47.143
- And we can have job stuff
happen after the age of 30.

30:47.179 --> 30:49.079
- And hidden desires.

30:49.214 --> 30:51.615
There's no age limit on that.

30:53.485 --> 30:55.319
- Huh?

30:55.321 --> 31:00.223
♪♪♪

31:00.292 --> 31:01.892
- Okay, fine!

31:02.027 --> 31:04.294
You want to know about davide?!

31:04.429 --> 31:06.363
He kissed me!

31:06.498 --> 31:08.831
And dammit if yoni didn't
groan back from the dead!

31:08.868 --> 31:10.467
- Okay! (laughs)
- oh my god!

31:12.638 --> 31:14.438
- (sighs) god damn it,
I'm walking home.

31:14.573 --> 31:16.640
- So wait, you sucked face
with him?

31:16.642 --> 31:18.942
- He sucked face with me.
- Did he linger?

31:18.978 --> 31:21.144
- Was there tongue?
- Where the hell was dad?

31:21.280 --> 31:23.179
- Upstage right.

31:23.215 --> 31:25.982
But he'd rather fix the water
heater in the change house

31:26.118 --> 31:27.851
Than the one in my pants!

31:27.853 --> 31:29.720
Oh, hell,

31:29.855 --> 31:31.854
If it isn't nice to feel
attractive again.

31:31.891 --> 31:33.990
- You know, dad's obsession
with the water heater

31:34.059 --> 31:35.992
Is because he's obsessed
with you.

31:36.028 --> 31:37.994
He equates his attractiveness
to being useful,

31:38.130 --> 31:40.330
That and his self-worth
went kaput

31:40.366 --> 31:41.999
With this whole retirement
thing.

31:42.134 --> 31:44.267
Men have water heaters too,
you know, in their pants!

31:44.270 --> 31:46.536
- Who is this wise,
advice-giving woman?

31:46.538 --> 31:48.138
- And what have done
with our sister?

31:48.273 --> 31:50.140
- Foxton's answer to dr. Ruth.

31:50.209 --> 31:51.942
- Ah, well, at least
there's that.

31:52.077 --> 31:53.810
My job is about to destroy

31:53.879 --> 31:55.612
The only great relationship
I ever had.

31:55.747 --> 31:57.080
- What, so now it's a great
relationship?

31:57.082 --> 31:58.815
- Um, spill?

31:58.884 --> 32:00.717
Now.

32:00.786 --> 32:03.420
- Fine, I... I don't...

32:03.555 --> 32:05.622
Hate co-habitation.

32:05.757 --> 32:08.024
Or the fact that a man
cares about me a lot.

32:09.395 --> 32:12.229
He stocks my fridge with more
than just boxed wine,

32:12.231 --> 32:13.964
And hot sauce.

32:14.099 --> 32:16.099
He picks up sharp objects
from the floor,

32:16.234 --> 32:18.235
He closes the windows
when it rains,

32:18.237 --> 32:21.171
Unclogs my hair from the
drains, I love all of it.

32:21.306 --> 32:23.306
I...

32:23.309 --> 32:24.908
(sighs)

32:24.977 --> 32:27.911
I... Really love terry.

32:28.046 --> 32:30.981
- Isn't that a good thing?
- No, it blows!

32:31.116 --> 32:33.784
I-- oh!

32:33.786 --> 32:37.187
Some big media company
offered me a job in l.A.

32:37.256 --> 32:39.122
- (gasps) what?
- Yeah.

32:39.124 --> 32:40.390
They heard my new show,

32:40.525 --> 32:42.959
They dug my real voice,
or some shit.

32:42.962 --> 32:45.728
Offered me ten times
what I make at cove-fm.

32:45.764 --> 32:48.631
But I can't...

32:48.667 --> 32:51.234
Choose a man over my career.

32:52.271 --> 32:54.004
Can I? Like, I--

32:54.139 --> 32:55.872
It's...

32:56.008 --> 32:57.074
No, see?

32:57.209 --> 32:59.009
This is exactly why
I didn't say anything.

33:00.112 --> 33:01.911
- You and terry will
be fine, nora.

33:01.947 --> 33:04.214
- Will we? Confession may
cleanse the soul,

33:04.349 --> 33:06.082
But it doesn't solve shit!

33:06.118 --> 33:08.552
- Of course it does!
It's purging.

33:08.687 --> 33:10.620
- How the hell would you know?!

33:11.957 --> 33:13.890
We came here for you,
but we're the ones

33:13.926 --> 33:15.658
Telling the ugly truth!

33:17.029 --> 33:18.595
- Wait, where are you going?

33:18.664 --> 33:20.230
- Back to the cabin.

33:20.299 --> 33:22.599
We're never gonna find
the stupid keys.

33:23.702 --> 33:25.435
- Okay, fine!

33:25.570 --> 33:27.503
The moonshine is in trouble!

33:30.843 --> 33:33.844
So, yeah, maybe I've been
acting a little erratic lately,

33:33.846 --> 33:35.612
But it's not because
I'm gaga for gale.

33:37.149 --> 33:39.482
I'm trying to take
my birthright seriously,

33:39.551 --> 33:41.984
And save this family from ruin.
Again.

33:42.021 --> 33:44.588
- But lobsterpalooza,
bingo night, we cashed in.

33:44.723 --> 33:46.389
- It's true, it feels like

33:46.392 --> 33:48.091
We're finally digging ourselves
out of the hole.

33:48.160 --> 33:50.460
- The hole is deeper
than we thought.

33:52.231 --> 33:54.164
- How deep?

33:54.233 --> 33:55.966
- $350k deep.

33:55.968 --> 33:57.533
- Oh.

33:57.569 --> 34:01.071
♪♪♪

34:04.409 --> 34:06.743
Row caws)

34:06.745 --> 34:09.212
♪♪♪

